Everyone who serves in the U.S. military sees firsthand things that just are invisible to civilians. The same is true for dependents and family members. For example, try explaining to a civilian the concept of &ldquo;hurry up and wait.&rdquo;
Sadly, one fact that service members, veterans, and their dependents know is that Air Force, Army, and Navy hospital health care often miss the mark when compared with civilian hospitals.
I know that I witnessed this myself.
